article.headline: Elon University 80, East Tenn. St. 72
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Le'Vonn Jordan scored 20 points and gathered 10 rebounds to lead Elon to an 80-72 win Monday over East Tennessee State. Jordan and the Phoenix kept getting to the foul line, extending their 36-34 halftime lead. Elon (5-19, 3-8 Southern Conference) made 19 of 32 free throw attempts, compared to 14 of 18 from the stripe for ETSU (6-15, 2-9). ETSU hit a field goal at the buzzer to cut the final margin to 8 points. Tim Smith led the Buccaneers with 32 points and Ben Rhoda had 18. No other ETSU player scored more than 6 points. Elon's Brian Waters had 18 points and Chris Chalko added 14.
